  "title": "Mechanical Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong><br />\nThe role involves supervising ACMV and mechanical installation works on-site, coordinating daily activities with engineers and subcontractors, and ensuring all works comply with project specifications, quality standards, and safety requirements.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>·     Supervise and coordinate daily site activities for ACMV and mechanical installations.</p><p>·     Ensure all mechanical works are executed according to approved drawings, method statements, and project specifications.</p><p>·     Monitor workmanship quality and resolve site issues in a timely manner.</p><p>·     Coordinate with engineers, subcontractors, suppliers, and other site teams to achieve project progress targets.</p><p>·     Conduct site inspections to ensure compliance with quality, safety, and regulatory requirements.</p><p>·     Assist in preparing site reports, progress updates, and project documentation.</p><p>·     Support testing and commissioning activities for mechanical systems.</p><p>·     Ensure enforcement of safe work practices and adherence to EHS requirements.<br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>·      Diploma or ITE Certificate in Mechanical Engineering, Building Services, or a related field.</p><p>·      Minimum 5 years of experience supervising ACMV/mechanical works in construction or industrial projects.</p><p>·      Sound understanding of ACMV systems, ducting, piping, and mechanical equipment installation.</p><p>·      Ability to read and interpret mechanical drawings and technical documents.</p><p>·      Strong communication and leadership skills to manage site teams and subcontractors.</p><p>·      Familiarity with site safety, QA/QC procedures, and regulatory requirements.</p><p>·      Willingness to work at Tuas with transportation pick up at designated MRT station.</p>",
